      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense for their prep. one thing my students struggle with is when the opposition tries to dismiss those points as being \"anti-humanitarian\" or \"xenophobic.\" how would a debater from the pro-enforcement side respond to the claim that prioritizing national identity over the plight of individual migrants is fundamentally unethical? i want them to have a sophisticated rebuttal that doesn't just sound like they're ignoring the human element.",
